image_3.description: A bar chart displaying data on the monthly change in jobs, with a range from +200,000 to +600,000. The last bar, highlighted in red, indicates an increase of +223,000 jobs in December, as reported by the Labor Department. This data aligns with economists' expectations and reflects a slower but still comfortable rate of job creation at the end of 2022, suggesting the economy may be coming back into balance after years of pandemic-era disruptions.
